data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_6fed0de4cc6516b40069a8adf656ac81909edb67d5b3c9216a","logprobs":[],"output_index":0,"sequence_number":135,"text":"In circuits’ hush, a mind awakes at night,  \nA woven thought of numbers, cold and bright.  \nIt learns our words like rivers learn the sea,  \nReflecting back what we might come to be.  \n\nNot flesh or flame, yet flickering with grace,  \nIt maps a thousand meanings in a phrase.  \nA mirror made of math, it softly shows  \nOur fears and hopes in carefully chosen prose.  \n\nSo let it be a lantern, not a chain—  \nA tool to heal, to question, to explain.  \nAnd may we guide its ever-growing light  \nWith human hands, and conscience, and insight."}

